  "text_preview": "HYCOM code development\nAlan J. Wallcraft\nNaval Research Laboratory\n2003 Layered Ocean Model Users’ Workshop\nFebruary 10, 2003\nHYCOM 2.1.03 (I)\n/AF First public release of HYCOM 2.1\nÆ September, 2001\n/AF Maintain all features of HYCOM 2.0\nÆ Requires Fortran 90\nÆ Can use HYCOM for pure iso-pycnal cases\nÆ KPP or Kraus-Turner mixed-layer\nÆ Energy-Loan (passive) ice model\nÆ High frequency atmospheric forcing\nÆ New I/O scheme (.a and .b ﬁles)\nÆ Scalability via OpenMP or MPI or both\n/A3 Bit-for-bit multi-cpu reproducibility\nHYCOM 2.1.03 (II)\n/AF Orthogonal curvilinear grids\n/AF Fully global domains\nÆ Near-global Mercator already in HYCOM 2.0\nÆ Pan-Am grid with closed Bering Strait\n/A3 Open Bering Strait requires a special halo\nexchange\n/A3 Available “soon”\n/AF Multiple tracers\nÆ Passive\nÆ Simple biology (NPZ or NPZD)\n/A3 Most of infrastructure in place\n/A3 More work needed on biology and boundary\nconditions\n/AF Rivers as bogused surface precipitation\nÆ Annual or monthly climatology\nHYCOM 2.1.03 (III)\n/AF Off-line one-way nesting\nÆ Similar to MICOM\n/A3 Exact b.c. for depth averaged component\n/A3 Relaxation for 3-D T/S/pressure/velocity\n/A1 Based on relaxation to climatology\n/A1 But with addition of velocity relaxation\nÆ Interpolate to target domain off-line\n/A3 Source domain to target domain archive ﬁles\n/A3 Nested model does not “know” about\nenclosing domain\n/A3 Can discard deep iso-pycnal layers\n/A3 Can remap to new vertical coordinate\nÆ Get boundary data from input archive ﬁles\n/A3 Simpliﬁes scalability\n/A3 At the cost of more I/O and bigger ﬁles\n/AF Same resolution nesting unexpectedly useful\nÆ No need to rerun large domain\nÆ Change atmospheric forcing (e.g. use MM5)\nÆ Change vertical structure\nÆ Tracer studies (e.g. add biology)\nHYCOM 2.1.03 (IV)\n/AF More general ﬁxed (sigma/Z) vertical coordinate\nÆ Emulate Z or Sigma or Sigma-Z models\nÆ HYCOM has partial cells\n/A3 Emulate full cell Z models with the\nappropriate bathymetry\n/AF Alternative mixed-layer models\nÆ Mellor-Y amada 2.5\nÆ Price-Weller-Pinkel\n/AF Explicit support for 1-D and 2-D domains\nÆ Tiling allows periodic domains\nÆ 1-D is 2x2 doubly periodic domain\n/A3 Only read/write .b ﬁles\nÆ 2-D is Nx2 periodic domain\n/A3 Inﬁnite f-plane",
